Project Summary

Project Information

FieldValue
NameInitiator
DescriptionjSCSI is a feature-complete iSCSI implementation in Java only. Platform-independent and fast, jSCSI represents a premium example how low-level protocols can be pushed to higher levels. jSCSI contains a server (target), a client (initiator) and common classes to work with the protocol.
Homepagehttp://disy.github.com/jSCSI/
